From M.van_iterson.HG at lumc.nl  Mon Jan  3 13:12:28 2011
From: M.van_iterson.HG at lumc.nl (Maarten van Iterson)
Date: Mon, 3 Jan 2011 13:12:28 +0100
Subject: [Bioc-devel] TurboNorm: new package for fast normalization of whole
 genome arrays
Message-ID: <1294056748.2017.17.camel@5-hkg-09-0007>

Dear all, 

I would like to introduce a package "TurboNorm" for fast normalization
of whole genome arrays based on P-splines. Here is a short description:

Among the most commonly applied microarray normalization methods are
intensity-dependent normalization methods such as lowess or loess
algorithms. Their computational complexity makes them slow and thus less
suitable for normalization of large datasets. We developed a novel
intensity-dependent normalization method for microarrays that is fast,
simple and can include weighing of observations. Our novel
intensity-dependent normalization method is simpler and faster than
current loess algorithms, and can be applied to both one- and two-colour
array data, similar to normalization based on loess. 

Kind regards, 

