Subject: [Bioc-devel] Bioc course: Advanced R Programming, 17-18 Feb, Seattle
Message-ID: <4D31A380.2070000@fhcrc.org>

Bioconductors,

We'll be offering a course 'Advanced R Programming' on 17-18 February,
in Seattle. This unique workshop provides advanced users with resources
for producing effective, reusable software packages in R / Bioconductor.
Participants are expected to be familiar with programming language
concepts, a good understanding of R, and familiarity with Bioconductor.
Topics include efficient R programming, R's object-oriented systems,
interfacing with common resources, integrating compiled code, and
organizing software into robust, reusable packages.

More information and registration is available at

https://secure.bioconductor.org/SeattleFeb11/

See you in Seattle!

Martin
